highlights.description: As an African-American woman, I have had one of the best experiences living here in Madison, Wisconsin
God kept me here in Madison on purpose to be a light in a dark place
LaTanya's comment grabbed my attention because it emphasized the opportunities here in Madison as well as the communal atmosphere.
Everett shares a vulnerable moment in his life that has shaped him and his family.
The few times Nancy saw people of color growing up were when migrant kids came into town.  They would be in town temporarily, presumably only in season.
LaTanya shares her experiences in Madison as an African-American woman.  She states she's had tremendous opportunity and that people have treated her with care.
Pastor Everett shares that in Madison he has been able to move forward in life in ways that many other black men are unable to in different parts of the country.
Nancy voices frustration over the lack of teaching on the history of black Americans in the U.S.
Pastor Everett speaks to the issue that in Madison, intersectionality is more intentional than in places in the South (i.e. Texas.)
